commit.message:
Surrounds negative numbers with parentheses when necessary

This behavior is consistent with Show instances of integral types in
base and allows the result of `show` to be parsed as Haskell code.
The added test used to fail and now passes:

```
    show (Just (-1)):                   FAIL
      test/test.hs:116:
      expected: "Just (-1.0)"
       but got: "Just -1.0"
```

Normalize Scientific numbers on construction

Fixes #63

Also expose the new Unsafe module `Data.Scientific.Unsafe` which exports
`unsafeScientificFromNormalized` for constructing Scientific numbers
from an already normalized coefficient.
Add tests for the DoS protection
Disable the tests on GHC < 8 because tasty-ant-xml fails to build

fromRational: fail instead of diverge on repeating decimals

Fixes #64
Improved documentation by adding safety instructions
Make Hashable, Eq and Ord safe when dealing with huge exponents
Disable benchmarks on travis because cabal can't find an install plan

Dropped upper version bounds of dependencies

It's to much work to maintain.

Bumped upper bound version for base.

Fix compilation with GHC 8.4.1 (tested with GHC 8.4.1-alpha1).
